*@johnpryan commented on Aug 30, 2019, 2:58 PM UTC:*

On the master channel, the "Open Widget Sample" feature creates the Counter sample, not the sample that was selected.

## Steps to Reproduce

1.  open the Flutter framework package in IntelliJ
2.  Navigate to src/material/chips.dart
3.  select the onDeleted widget sample and hit "Go..."

[![Screen Shot 2019-08-30 at 7 49 09 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1145719/64030591-bf80c480-cafb-11e9-81c7-32af1f920fc3.png)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1145719/64030591-bf80c480-cafb-11e9-81c7-32af1f920fc3.png)

4.  Observe that the sample is the counter sample, not the sample in the docs.

## Flutter doctor output


*@RedBrogdon commented on Aug 30, 2019, 5:45 PM UTC:*

CC: @gspencergoog

*@gspencergoog commented on Aug 30, 2019, 5:52 PM UTC:*

CC @devoncarew

I was just testing this and I can confirm it. The default `Counter sample` is being created. I debugged a little and found out the command that was being used to create a new app (`flutter create --template app --description "Some Description" /path/to/new/project`) didn't have the `--sample` argument. Is that the cause?
Ah!  Good catch @frextrite.  There were some refactorings in this area and I wonder if that regressed.  (I'm confident that at least at one point we were properly threading that through...) ðŸ¤”

Only just saw this, but looks like it was IntelliJ-specific.  VS Code passes `--sample` [here](https://github.com/Dart-Code/Dart-Code/blob/9aca43ff8715392db2450fb9564859f2b937341a/src/extension/commands/sdk.ts#L216).
Yep, @frextrite fixed it on the IntelliJ side.  Cheers @DanTup!

title: "Open Widget Sample" in IntelliJ creates the Counter sample
